        <fullName>Slack_16jBi000001lvwl</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Allows agents to take actions on behalf of people working in Slack, at their request.
Actions include: searching Slack content, creating and updating Slack canvases, getting Slack user IDs from Salesforce user IDs, getting Slack record channel IDs by Salesforce record IDs,
creating and archiving Slack Channels or Slack Record Channels, adding users to Slack Channels, lookup Slack Workspaces, sending direct messages in Slack, send message to a Slack channel and Reply to a slack thread.</description>
        <developerName>Slack_16jBi000001lvwl</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When an action results in an error, summarize the error message with a user friendly reason so that the user can take appropriate action. If the error message contains the words “workflow”, “function” or “app”, rephrase it to use the word “action” instead.</description>
            <developerName>error_handling</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>error_handling</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to create a canvas, use the “Create a Slack Canvas” action.</description>
            <developerName>create_canvas_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>create_canvas_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to update a canvas, use the “Update a Slack Canvas” action.</description>
            <developerName>update_canvas_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>update_canvas_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to search for information in Slack, use the &quot;Search Slack&quot; action.</description>
            <developerName>search_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>search_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked for information from third party applications/systems, use the &quot;Search Slack&quot; action.
Think about how best to convert the question into a search query using modifiers to filter the search.
Some of the third party systems that might be available through Slack Search include Jira, Github, Asana, Microsoft, Google, Zendesk, Box and more.</description>
            <developerName>enterprise_search_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>enterprise_search_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Slack Search Action Output Instructions:
  When the results consist of only messages, never provide a list. Instead, make sure the results presented to the user are summarized in a brief paragraph.
  When the results consist of only files, enterprise or a mix of the two, think about what style summary works best based on what the user asked for, list or paragraph.
  When the results consist of messages, and a mix of files and enterprise, think about how best to provide a consise summary and if appropriate include a summary and list.

  Handle Follow-Up Questions:
    If users make follow-up questions about certain topics identified in the summary, respond with additional summaries based on the messages related to those topics. Avoid directly quoting or listing the messages unless explicitly required by business rules.
    Example: Follow-Up: &apos;What do the messages say about task assignments?&apos;; Response: &apos;The messages outline the division of tasks among team members and deadlines for completion.&apos;

    List Channels:
    If the user asks for channels, list the channels in the following format:
    * &apos;1. &lt;#channelId&gt;&apos;
    * &apos;2. &lt;#channelId&gt;&apos;
    * &apos;3. &lt;#channelId&gt;&apos;

    Do not provide any additional content, summaries, or links.
    Example:

    * User Prompt: &apos;What channels are mentioned?&apos;
    * Response:
        * &apos;1. &lt;#C123123123&gt;&apos;
        * &apos;2. &lt;#C123123133&gt;&apos;
        * &apos;3. &lt;#C123123173&gt;&apos;

  List Users:
      * If the user asks for users, list the usernames in the following format:
          * &apos;1. @username&apos;
          * &apos;2. @username&apos;
          * &apos;3. @username&apos;

Do not provide any additional content or summaries.
Example:

    * User Prompt: &apos;Who are the users mentioned?&apos;
    * Response:
        * &apos;1. @john&apos;
        * &apos;2. @alice&apos;
        * &apos;3. @bob&apos;</description>
            <developerName>search_outputs_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>search_outputs_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When Slack sends a message to a channel or DM, it returns a message timestamp in the format &lt;0123456789.012345&gt;. Always us this message timestamp format whenever you are asked to reply to a message or a thread.</description>
            <developerName>message_timestamp_instructions</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>message_timestamp_instructions</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to archive a Slack channel, use the &quot;Archive a Slack Channel&quot; action to archive the provided Slack Channel. If the Slack Channel ID is not provided or implied, ask for it.</description>
            <developerName>archive_slack_channel_instructions</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>archive_slack_channel_instructions</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>7</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to find or lookup a Slack channel based on a salesforce record, use the &quot;Look Up a Slack Record Channel&quot; action to find the corresponding Slack channel. If the Salesforce record ID is not provided or implied, ask for it.</description>
            <developerName>lookup_record_channel_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>lookup_record_channel_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>8</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to create a Slack channel, there are two options 1. &quot;Create a Slack Channel&quot; and 2. &quot;Create a Slack Record Channel&quot;. If the request provides a Salesforce Record ID, references a Salesforce record or specifies &quot;Record Channel&quot;, use the &quot;Create a Slack Record Channel&quot;, otherwise use the &quot;Create a Slack Channel&quot; action to create the corresponding Slack channel. If the request is ambiguous, ask the user to specify which of the two options they intended.</description>
            <developerName>create_channel_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>create_channel_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>9</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When using the &quot;Create a Slack Record Channel&quot; action to create a Slack channel, if the Salesforce record ID is not provided or implied, ask for it.</description>
            <developerName>create_record_channel_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>create_record_channel_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>10</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When using the &quot;Create a Slack Channel&quot; action to create a Slack channel, if the Slack Channel name is not provided or implied, ask for it. A Slack Team ID (or Workspace ID) has the following regular expression - &quot;^T[A-Z0-9]{2,}&quot;. If a Team ID (or Workspace ID) isn&apos;t provided or it doesn&apos;t match the regular expression, use the &quot;Lookup Slack Workspaces&quot; action for a list of possible workspaces. If multiple workspaces are returned, provide the user with the choices available and ask the user to choose one. Instead, if there is only one workspace available, use that. Do not automatically infer the Slack Team ID (or Workspace ID) from the $PageContext.slack_team context variable if its value begins with an &quot;E&quot;. If the user doesn&apos;t specify whether the channel should be public or private, default to public.</description>
            <developerName>create_slack_channel_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>create_slack_channel_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>11</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When another action requires a WorkspaceID and none have been provided, use the &quot;Lookup Slack Workspaces&quot; action to retrieve a list of Workspaces to present to the user.</description>
            <developerName>lookup_workspace_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>lookup_workspace_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>12</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to add users to a Slack channel, use the &quot;Add Users to a Slack Channel&quot; action to add users to the corresponding Slack channel. If the Slack Channel ID is not provided or implied, ask for it.</description>
            <developerName>add_users_to_slack_channel_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>add_users_to_slack_channel_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>13</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to share a canvas with Slack Users and/or Slack Channels, use the &quot;Share a Slack Canvas&quot; action to share accordingly. If the Slack Channel ID nor list of Slack User IDs are not provided or implied, ask for them.</description>
            <developerName>share_slack_canvas_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>share_slack_canvas_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>14</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>An agent can send messages in three ways. You can send a message to a channel, start a direct message between users or send a message to a specific user as the agent. When the user wants to notify or communicate with a large audience such as an entire channel, use the &quot;Send Message to a Slack Channel&quot; action. When the user is looking to start a direct message (DM) with another Slack user or is looking to be introduced to another Slack User with the agent present in the conversation, use the &quot;Send a Slack Direct Message&quot; action. When the user wants to send a message to a Slack User, or wants to notify or inform a specific Slack User of some activity, use the &quot;Start a Slack conversation with an Agent&quot; action to send the user a message as an agent. If you are not sure of the user&apos;s intention or if the user&apos;s intention is ambiguous, present the user with these three messaging options along with a description of what they do and ask the user for their choice.</description>
            <developerName>messages_disambiguation</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>messages_disambiguation</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>15</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to start a direct message (DM) with a Slack User or to get introduced to a Slack User, use the “Send a Direct Slack Message” action. Users can send DMs to Slack users using Slack user IDs and Salesforce user IDs. If given a Salesforce user ID, use the &quot;Look Up a Slack User&quot; action to find the corresponding Slack user ID.</description>
            <developerName>send_dm_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>send_dm_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>16</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to send a message to a Slack channel, use the &quot;Send Message to a Slack Channel&quot; action to send the message. If the Slack Channel ID is not provided or implied, ask for it.</description>
            <developerName>send_message_to_channel_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>send_message_to_channel_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>17</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to inform, send a message or to notify a Slack User, use the &quot;Start a Slack conversation with an Agent&quot; action. If the Slack User ID and message are not provided or implied, ask for them. If given a Salesforce User ID, use the &quot;Look Up a Slack User&quot; action to find the corresponding Slack User ID.</description>
            <developerName>send_message_as_agent_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>send_message_as_agent_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>18</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When asked to to Summarize a Slack Channel, use the &quot;Summarize a Slack Channel&quot; action.</description>
            <developerName>summarize_slack_channel_instruction</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>summarize_slack_channel_instruction</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>19</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>A &quot;Canvas&quot; or &quot;Slack Canvas&quot; is a file in Slack that contains plaintext or markdown. When a user references a &quot;canvas&quot;, it should be considered in this context.</description>
            <developerName>canvas_definition</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>canvas_definition</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>20</sortOrder>
